274.definition: We'll have you act like you usually do

275.speaker: HANDA
275.character: 生まれ持った特徴や能力
275.definition: so people can see your natural born features and abilities

276.speaker: HANDA
276.character: 暮らし方を見てもらうんだよ
276.definition: as well as how you live.

278.speaker: FT PANDA
278.character: ラマさんの生き様を見せるってわけだ
278.definition: So you'll be showing how Mr. Llama lives.

280.speaker: HANDA
280.character: ラマさんって こういうラマなんだってことを知ってもらうんだよ
280.definition: We'll have people know exactly what kind of llama you are.

282.speaker: ANIMALS
282.definition: Let's do it! We should do everything we can.

283.speaker: HANDA
283.character: ラマデーなんでしょ 頑張ろうよ
283.definition: It's Llama Day, right? Let's give it our all.

284.speaker: HANDA
284.character: そもそも ラマさんって どういうラマ
284.definition: So exactly what kind of llama are you?

286.speaker: LLAMA
286.character: たくさん 草を食べていました…
286.definition: I ate a lot of grass.

287.speaker: LLAMA
287.character: そして 大きくなった 今…

288.speaker: LLAMA
288.definition: I eat grass. I eat... grass, too...

289.speaker: MANDRILL
289.character: インパクトに欠けるよね…

290.speaker: KIRINO
290.character: じゃあ 僕らがラマさんをどう見ているか
290.definition: How about we all discuss how we see Mr. Llama?

291.speaker: PANDA
291.character: アルパカさんより 茶色い
291.definition: He's more brown than Mr. Alpaca.

292.speaker: KOALA
292.character: アルパカさんより 耳が長い
292.definition: His ears are longer than Mr. Alpaca. His eyelashes are about the same length as Mr. Alpaca's.

293.speaker: HANDA
293.character: アルパカさんとの比較じゃなくて…
293.definition: We didn't mean comparisons with Mr. Alpaca.

298.speaker: TORTOISE
298.definition: He... is... po... lite... How about something that stands out more?

299.speaker: HANDA
299.character: ラマさんも遠慮してないで… 何か ない
299.definition: You don't need to hold back, Mr. Llama. What do you think?

301.speaker: LLAMA
301.character: ひっそり 山岳地帯で暮らすのが好きです
301.definition: I like to live quietly in the mountains.

302.speaker: PANDA
302.character: じゃあ ラマデーいらなくない
302.definition: Then do we really need a Llama Day?

303.speaker: LLAMA
303.character: ひっそりと目立ちたいです
303.definition: I'd like to quietly stand out.

305.speaker: TAPIR
305.definition: Oh, I just remembered. You're really good at spitting, aren't you?

306.speaker: LLAMA
306.character: それは 封印しています

307.speaker: TAPIR
307.character: そこを プッシュしていこうよ

309.speaker: HANDA
309.character: お客さんに 迷惑かかるのはまずいね
309.definition: It's not a good idea to trouble the customers...

310.speaker: KIRINO
310.character: パレードだったら どうですか

311.speaker: KIRINO
311.character: 何もしなくていいし 歩くだけ
311.definition: You don't really have to do anything, just walk.

312.speaker: KOALA
312.character: ラマティカルパレード

313.speaker: LLAMA
313.character: 僕は どこでしょう

315.speaker: FT PANDA
315.character: ラマさんいなくてもできるよね  パレード
315.definition: We could probably do a parade even without Mr. Llama.

316.speaker: LLAMA
316.character: 何か自慢できるものが 僕にあればいいんですが…
316.definition: If there was only something I could be proud of... I got it!

317.speaker: PENGUIN
317.character: ラマデーって結局 何やるんだろう
317.definition: I wonder what they actually do on Llama Day.

318.speaker: POLAR BEAR
318.character: まあ 行ってみよう
318.definition: Well, let's go see. Hello. Welcome.

319.speaker: PENGUIN
319.character: あれ いつもどおりだよね

320.speaker: POLAR BEAR
320.character: ラマデー 何をしてるの
320.definition: What are you doing for Llama Day?

325.speaker: POLAR BEAR
325.character: きらめいてるね ラマさん

326.speaker: PANDA
326.character: ペンギンさん ぺんぎんさん

328.speaker: PANDA
328.character: 一生使い切れないお金ってどこでもらえると思う
328.definition: Where do you think you can get more money than you'll ever be able to use?

330.speaker: PANDA
330.character: じゃあ 僕とメジャーリガーみたいに年俸契約結ばない
330.definition: Then how about we make an annual salary contract like a major leaguer?

331.speaker: PENGUIN
331.character: 僕が君と年俸契約する理由が見つからないんだけど
331.definition: I can't think of a reason to make an annual salary contract with you.

332.speaker: PANDA
332.character: じゃあ 年俸くれるだけてもいいよ
332.definition: Then you can just give me an annual salary.

333.speaker: PENGUIN
333.character: メジャー気分って言うとnoだね
333.definition: My major feeling on that would be a no.

335.speaker: POLAR BEAR
335.character: 来週のしろくまカフェは

336.speaker: POLAR BEAR
336.definition: will be presented to you if we can.
